getMIMETypeIcon

public Resource getMIMETypeIcon(java.lang.String mimeType,
                                java.lang.String filename)
Get icon for given file type.
The file type is first checked by the MIME type provided. If no matches are found, the filename extension is checked next.
If that neither is recognized, a generic icon is returned.

Parameters:
mimeType - the MIME type of the file
filename - the name of the file with file extension included
Returns:
the icon for the given document type.
